text: Medical Centers, Clinics, and Clinicians: Build confidence in #COVID19 vaccines among your healthcare teams. Educate your staff and provide them with the tools to promote COVID-19 vaccination to healthcare workers and patients: https://t.co/OhhilfC2HE https://t.co/xQrkjZsyiY

Healthcare Personnel: It’s important that you get vaccinated against #COVID19 as soon as possible. If you are directly involved in patient care or indirectly exposed to patients or infectious materials, you should get vaccinated as soon as you can. More: https://t.co/jVFqVSUQTQ https://t.co/OoWdTlJF53
RT @CDCDirector: As of January 26, 2021, almost 20 million people had received their first dose of #COVID19 vaccine. Of those, over 3 milli…

Vaccination providers: Have appropriate medical supplies to treat severe allergic reaction immediately available during #COVID19 vaccine administration & in observation area in the event of an acute anaphylactic reaction. See interim considerations:  https://t.co/ezmgeL7Y8b

#HCPs: Patients with a history of immediate allergic reaction to a vaccine other than COVID-19 vaccine, or anaphylaxis due to any cause, may get an mRNA #COVID19 vaccine. However, they should be observed for 30 minutes after vaccination. https://t.co/La7waJUs6v

#HCPs: Make sure your patients continue to #WearAMask, stay at least 6 ft apart, and avoid crowds after getting vaccinated. We need to continue using all the tools available to help stop this pandemic. https://t.co/ycq7Z94uxR

It’s crucial that staff and residents of long-term care facilities receive a #COVID19 vaccine as soon as possible. I applaud everyone’s efforts to make sure those at greatest risk of infection are vaccinated, and I am glad to see these vaccination numbers continue to increase. https://t.co/1IoueQ3gQA

On Jan. 27, 2021, members of the Advisory Committee on Immunization Practices (ACIP) will meet to discuss #COVID19 vaccine safety updates and effectiveness studies, among other topics. Join live beginning at 10 AM ET: https://t.co/1egG4Qvmua https://t.co/4mlIf9359A

As of January 25, 2021, more than 19 million people had received at least one dose of a #COVID19 vaccine. Of those, over 3 million had received both doses and are fully vaccinated. See more vaccination data at @CDCgov COVID Data tracker: https://t.co/FHGplToHFM https://t.co/cRui9qWBBJ

#HCPs: As our nation’s frontline defense in the fight against #COVID19, it is essential that you protect both yourself and your patients by getting the COVID-19 vaccine. Learn more about the importance of COVID-19 vaccination: https://t.co/jVFqVSUQTQ https://t.co/3acyrt6Qle
Join Prof Barry Bloom, Dr Sandy Nelson, @mlipsitch, @SCOTTeHENSLEY, and me today at 12pm ET as we talk about what’s ahead for #COVID19 vaccine rollout. No registration needed. https://t.co/8x6eaB5yfT

So glad to have Dr. Rochelle Walensky join @CDCgov. 
I look forward to working with you, @CDCDirector, to end the #COVID19 pandemic and expand the agency’s work on vaccine confidence. https://t.co/DIyiy06fpy

.@CDCgov’s recommendations for who should get vaccinated first were made to:
-Decrease death and serious disease 
-Keep society functioning
-Reduce the extra burden of #COVID19 on people already facing disparities

More: https://t.co/vDRyBIUHme https://t.co/g4pYdZqEUO

.@CDCgov’s COVID Data Tracker now includes #COVID19 vaccination data for first and second doses. As of January 19, more than 13.5 million had received their first dose of a COVID-19 vaccine & more than 2 million of those had received two doses. More data: https://t.co/FHGplTGixk https://t.co/ze5vW0JKIX

Vaccinating #LongTermCare facility residents will help save the lives of those who are most at risk of dying from #COVID19. 

Facility Administrators: See @CDCgov’s toolkit to help you prepare for and promote vaccination in your facility:  https://t.co/li0NIUELgZ https://t.co/yfG2VKU755

#HCPs: Are you administering #COVID19 vaccines? Take these three on-demand training modules that share what you need to know about immunization best practices, Moderna COVID-19 vaccine, and Pfizer-BioNTech COVID-19 vaccine. https://t.co/Av4oVoC4xj https://t.co/c3wzGd9Rv7

#HCPs: Take time to review the latest interim clinical considerations for mRNA #COVID19 vaccines. Considerations include information on vaccinating people with previous infection or exposure and special populations, reporting adverse events, and more:  https://t.co/Z7hIOOrZCL https://t.co/mSdA7GEQNR

Staff members and residents of long-term care facilities are among those at greatest risk for infection from #COVID19. It’s crucial that they can be vaccinated as quickly as possible, and I congratulate our partner program on this important milestone. https://t.co/MjQpTaSE5j

@danahull @bhrenton @CDCgov The Bureau of Prisons (BOP) data on the COVID Data Tracker include vaccination of all full-time employees and incarcerated individuals based on ACIP recommendations and prioritization. For BOP strategy and guidance information, visit https://t.co/Mw9aYrOeRa

#HCPs: Your patients consider you their most trusted source on vaccines &sometimes they simply want your answers to their questions, especially when it comes to vaccine safety.

Learn more about answering common patient questions about #COVID19 vaccine: https://t.co/a8VfgFxXfF https://t.co/tmaWoT0Q7S

HCPs: Remember to provide the v-safe information sheet to patients after they receive their #COVID19 vaccination. Your encouragement to enroll makes a difference. 
https://t.co/PZb1Xsr8sG https://t.co/LCJOsLuMul

.@CDCgov’s COVID Data Tracker now includes #COVID19 vaccine distribution and administration data. As of January 11, 2021, nearly 9 million people had received their first dose of a COVID-19 vaccine. More on COVID-19 vaccination data: https://t.co/FHGplToHFM https://t.co/998c8M5FBK

@AndreaRaeLAc @CDCgov 2/2 All recipients of #COVID19 vaccine should be observed for at least 15 minutes after vaccination. People who have had an immediate allergic reaction—even if it was not severe—to an injectable medication should ask their doctor if they should get a COVID-19 vaccine.

@AndreaRaeLAc @CDCgov 1/2 Allergies to oral medications (including oral equivalents of injectable medications) are not a contraindication or precaution to vaccination with either mRNA #COVID19 vaccine. See https://t.co/ByanXQDz96

#HCPs: Recognize, respond, and report anaphylaxis after #COVID19 vaccination to VAERS—the nation’s early warning system for vaccine safety. Read @CDCgov’s interim considerations for recognition and treatment of anaphylaxis with COVID-19 vaccination: https://t.co/CnkPXwMGgg https://t.co/zRX5ExKGrp

The Federal Pharmacy Partnership for Long-Term Care Program began facilitating onsite #COVID19 vaccination clinics at #LongTermCare facilities across the U.S. in December. 
Learn more about the program: https://t.co/QVbqt17gjg https://t.co/lksrRJBfVz
Glad to join with the Black community to discuss COVID-19 vaccine protection during tonight’s virtual town hall (starts 7pm ET; 6pm CT). https://t.co/VEZxnE0uCL

As cases of #COVID19 continue to surge, I am happy and relieved to see so many healthcare providers and workers receive their #COVID19 vaccines. They are protecting themselves, their patients, and their families. I look forward to when it is my turn to roll my #SleeveUp. https://t.co/ReDE5Zgm8Y

#HCPs: Patients with weakened immune systems, autoimmune conditions, previously diagnosed with Guillain-Barre syndrome or Bell’s palsy may receive an mRNA #COVID19 vaccine. However, they should be aware of the limited safety data. Share @CDCgov resource: https://t.co/jkHbBYZDEj https://t.co/P2cFLCjGif

#LongTermCare Admins: As the Pharmacy Partnership for Long-Term Care Program COVID-19 vaccination clinics begin across the US, #LTC residents and staff may have questions. Use @CDCgov’s new toolkit to prepare: https://t.co/li0NIUELgZ https://t.co/vMCy15I4H8

.@CDCgov’s COVID Data Tracker now includes #COVID19 vaccination distribution and administration data. As of January 4, 2021, more than 4.5 million people have received their first dose of a COVID-19 vaccine. More on COVID-19 vaccination data: https://t.co/lcxlkHoCO6 https://t.co/c3GHVxabeu

2020 was a difficult year for us all, but recent events provide a reason for optimism. A year ago we heard about a new virus & now we have 2 vaccines in use. When you are eligible, I encourage you to roll your #SleeveUp for a #COVID19 vaccine. Have a safe, healthy new year!
